The linoleic acid content in the essential oils present in or extracted from a plant or the plant part such as seed.

definition.value: According to the Codex Alimentarium, the FAO international standards for food product specifications, the normal values may differ depending on the source plant. For example, in soybean oil the normal values for linoleic acid content are 48% - 59%.

value.value: The oleic acid content in the essential oils present in or extracted from a plant or the plant part such as seed.

definition.value: According to the Codex Alimentarium, the FAO international standards for food product specifications, the normal values may differ depending on the source plant. For example, for soybean oil the normal values for oleic acid content are 17% - 30%.

value.value: The stearic acid content in the essential oils present in or extracted from a plant or the plant part such as seed.

definition.value: According to the Codex Alimentarium, the FAO international standards for food product specifications, the normal values may differ depending on the source plant. e.g. for soybean oil the normal values for stearic acid content are 2% - 5.4%.

value.value: The omega-3 fatty acid content in the essential oils present in or extracted from a plant or the plant part such as seed.

definition.value: Omega-3 fatty acid (CHEBI:25681)  is a  polyunsaturated fatty acid (CHEBI:26208) . There are four subtypes of omega-3 fatty acids, namely,  alpha-licanic acid (CHEBI:28771), all-cis-docosa-4,7,10,13,16,19-hexaenoic acid (CHEBI:28125), all-cis-icosa-5,8,11,14,17-pentaenoic acid and alpha-linolenic acid (CHEBI:27432).
